<h2>ip.sudovim.com</h2>
<p>This will return the public IP that the request originates. This can be handy to not only get your IP, but used in scripts/automation. It is returned directly from Nginx as such:</p>
<code>server {<br />
listen 80;<br />
server_name ip.sudovim.com;<br />
add_header Content-Type text/plain;<br />
return 200 $remote_addr;<br />
}<br />
</code>
